CONJUGATES: I (nominative) | me (objective) | my (possessive determiner) | mine (possessive pronoun)
ETYMOLOGY: From Old English ic, from Proto-Germanic *ik, from Proto-Indo-European *eǵh₂.

MEANINGS.POS_TIP: A word that can function as a noun phrase referring to the participant speaking or writing.
MEANINGS.DEF_EN: The first-person singular nominative pronoun, used by a speaker or writer to refer to themselves.
MEANINGS.DEF_ZH: 第一人称单数主格代词，说话者或书写者用来指代自己。
MEANINGS.SENT_EN: I think I will go home now.

MEANINGS.POS_TIP: A word that refers to a person, place, thing, or idea.
MEANINGS.SENT_EN: Read Chapter I before our next class.
MEANINGS.SENT_ZH: 在下节课前阅读第一章。
